    "cost_rationale": "This incident response workflow requires multi-tool orchestration across AWS (CloudWatch, S3), Slack, and analytical capabilities. Five subtasks are minimal and necessary: (1) multitool_plan for CloudWatch inspection (mid tier due to conditional routing based on metrics), (2) multitool_plan for S3 log retrieval (mid tier due to cross-service coordination and data extraction), (3) multitool_plan for Slack channel creation (small tier\u2014straightforward API call), (4) cross_recon to synthesize CloudWatch + S3 findings into severity assessment (mid tier for multi-signal analysis), (5) multitool_plan to post formatted results (small tier). Dependencies enforce correct sequencing: service identification must precede log fetching and channel creation, both of which must complete before severity assessment, which must complete before Slack posting. This avoids redundant calls and respects the enterprise tool registry pattern."
